CTV Saskatoon.Title: Ford v Ferrari
CTV Saskatoon.Desc: An auto designer builds a revolutionary race car to compete against the Ferrari at the 1966 Le Mans.
CTV Saskatoon.LongDescription: American automotive designer Carroll Shelby and fearless British race car driver Ken Miles battle corporate interference, the laws of physics and their own personal demons to build a revolutionary vehicle for the Ford Motor Co. Together, they plan to compete against the race cars of Enzo Ferrari at the 24 Hours of Le Mans in France in 1966.
